<!-- Definition and symptoms -->
'''胎兒酒精譜系障礙'''（{{lang|en|Fetal alcohol spectrum disorders}}，簡稱'''FASDs'''）又稱'''胎兒酒精症候群'''，是母親在[[妊娠|妊娠]]期間[[酗酒|酗酒]]對[[胎兒|胎兒]]所造成的[[先天異常|先天異常]]<ref name=CDC2015Fact/>。症狀包含外觀異常、身材矮小、體重過輕、[[小頭畸形|小頭畸形]]、協調不佳、智力不足、行為異常，以及[[聾|聽覺]]及[[視力障礙|視覺受損]]<ref name=CDC2015Fact/><ref name=Canadian/>。成長期間可能出現就學及規範認知障礙、無法參與高風險活動，或濫用酒精及[[毒品|毒品]]問題<ref name=Cor2013>{{cite journal|last1=Coriale|first1=G|last2=Fiorentino|first2=D|last3=Di Lauro|first3=F|last4=Marchitelli|first4=R|last5=Scalese|first5=B|last6=Fiore|first6=M|last7=Maviglia|first7=M|last8=Ceccanti|first8=M|title=Fetal Alcohol Spectrum Disorder (FASD): neurobehavioral profile, indications for diagnosis and treatment.|journal=Rivista di psichiatria|date=2013|volume=48|issue=5|pages=359–69|pmid=24326748|doi=10.1708/1356.15062}}</ref>。其中最嚴重的是'''胎兒酒精綜合症'''（{{lang|en|Fetal Alcohol Syndrome}}，簡稱'''FAS'''）<ref name=CDC2015Fact/>，其他則包含'''部分胎兒酒精綜合症'''（{{lang|en|partial Fetal Alcohol Syndrome}}，簡稱'''pFAS'''）、'''酒精相關性神經發育障礙'''（{{lang|en|alcohol-related neurodevelopmental disorder}}，簡稱'''ARND'''）以及'''酒精相關性先天缺陷'''（{{lang|en|alcohol-related birth defects}}，簡稱'''ARBD'''）<ref name=CDC2015Fact>{{cite web|title=Facts about FASDs|url=http://www.cdc.gov/ncbddd/fasd/facts.html|accessdate=10 June 2015|date=April 16, 2015}}</ref><ref name=Ril2011/>。

<!-- Cause and diagnosis -->
胎兒酒精譜系障礙是因為孕婦在懷孕過程中飲酒造成<ref name=CDC2015Fact/>。[[美國|美國]]研究發現，10%的孕婦在待產的最後一個月曾經飲酒，20-30% 則曾在妊娠期間的某一時間飲酒<ref name=NIH2015/>。4.7% 的北美孕婦則甚至有[[酗酒|酗酒]]的現象<ref name=Mc2014>{{cite journal|last1=McHugh|first1=RK|last2=Wigderson|first2=S|last3=Greenfield|first3=SF|title=Epidemiology of substance use in reproductive-age women.|journal=Obstetrics and gynecology clinics of North America|date=June 2014|volume=41|issue=2|pages=177–89|pmid=24845483|doi=10.1016/j.ogc.2014.02.001}}</ref>。胎兒受影響的程度則取決於母親喝酒的份量、頻率及時間<ref name=NIH2015/>。其他風險則包含高齡孕婦、[[吸煙|吸煙]]，及飲食不均<ref name=NIH2015>{{cite web|title=Fetal Alcohol Exposure|url=http://pubs.niaaa.nih.gov/publications/FASDFactsheet/FASDfact.htm|accessdate=10 June 2015|date=April 2015|archive-date=2015-06-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150610050738/http://pubs.niaaa.nih.gov/publications/FASDFactsheet/FASDfact.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref>。目前沒有已知孕婦對於酒精的安全攝取量或安全攝取時間<ref name=CDC2015Fact/><ref name=Peds2015>{{cite journal|last1=Williams|first1=J. F.|last2=Smith|first2=V. C.|title=Fetal Alcohol Spectrum Disorders|journal=Pediatrics|date=19 October 2015|volume=136|issue=5|pages=e1395–e1406|doi=10.1542/peds.2015-3113}}</ref>。母體少量飲酒不會造成胎兒臉部發育異常，但仍可能導致行為問題<ref name=Mc2014/>。酒精可穿越[[血腦屏障|血腦屏障]]直接影響發育中的胎兒<ref>{{cite book|title=Fetal Alcohol Spectrum Disorder: Management and Policy Perspectives of FASD|date=2011|publisher=John Wiley & Sons|isbn=9783527632565|pages=73–75|url=https://books.google.ca/books?id=TiSL4txuYN0C&pg=PA73}}</ref>。診斷則須依賴症狀及徵象去判斷<ref name=CDC2015Fact/>。

<!-- Prevention and treatment -->
胎兒酒精譜系障礙可藉由禁止孕婦飲酒來避免<ref>{{cite web|title=Alcohol Use in Pregnancy|url=http://www.cdc.gov/ncbddd/fasd/alcohol-use.html|accessdate=10 June 2015|date=April 17, 2014}}</ref>，因此醫療院所及組織強烈建議禁止孕婦飲酒<ref name=SG>{{cite web|author1=Vice Admiral Richard H. Carmona|title=A 2005 Message to Women from the U.S. Surgeon General|url=http://www.cdc.gov/ncbddd/fasd/documents/sg-advisory.pdf|accessdate=12 June 2015|date=2005}}</ref><ref name=IOM>{{cite book|author1=Committee to Study Fetal Alcohol Syndrome, Division of Biobehavioral Sciences and Mental Disorders, Institute of Medicine|title=Fetal alcohol syndrome : diagnosis, epidemiology, prevention, and treatment|date=1995|publisher=National Academy Press|location=Washington, D.C.|isbn=0-309-05292-0|url=http://www.nap.edu/catalog/4991/fetal-alcohol-syndrome-diagnosis-epidemiology-prevention-and-treatment|access-date=2016-06-18|archive-date=2016-03-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160311182331/http://www.nap.edu/catalog/4991/fetal-alcohol-syndrome-diagnosis-epidemiology-prevention-and-treatment|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Australian Government National Health and Medical Research Council |url=http://www.nhmrc.gov.au/your-health/alcohol-guidelines |accessdate=4 November 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121105024533/http://www.nhmrc.gov.au/your-health/alcohol-guidelines |archive-date=2012-11-05 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。該疾病會導致胎兒永久性的傷害，但治療可以改善症狀<ref name=CDC2015Fact/>。介入治療包含[[亲子互动治疗|亲子互动治疗]]、行為矯治，可能也可以進行藥物治療<ref name=Roz2015>{{cite journal|last1=Roszel|first1=EL|title=Central nervous system deficits in fetal alcohol spectrum disorder.|journal=The Nurse practitioner|date=13 April 2015|volume=40|issue=4|pages=24–33|pmid=25774812|doi=10.1097/01.npr.0000444650.10142.4f}}</ref>。

<!-- Epidemiology and culture -->
胎兒酒精譜系障礙約影響美國和西歐 2-5% 的人口<ref name=CDC2015Prev/>。在美國平均每1,000名胎兒，就有 0.2 到 9 個FAS個案<ref name=CDC2015Prev/>。在[[南非|南非]]的某些族群甚至可能達到 9%<ref name=Ril2011/>。酒精的負面影響從遠古時代就有相關敘述<ref name=Ril2011>{{cite journal|last1=Riley|first1=EP|last2=Infante|first2=MA|last3=Warren|first3=KR|title=Fetal alcohol spectrum disorders: an overview.|journal=Neuropsychology review|date=June 2011|volume=21|issue=2|pages=73–80|pmid=21499711|doi=10.1007/s11065-011-9166-x}}</ref>。2002年，每名罹患FAS的孩童一輩子約需額外花費 $2,000,000 美金<ref name=CDC2015Prev>{{cite web|title=Data & Statistics Prevalence of FASDs|url=http://www.cdc.gov/ncbddd/fasd/data.html|website=Center for Disease Control and Prevention|accessdate=10 June 2015|date=April 16, 2015}}</ref>。「胎兒酒精綜合症」這個字最早於1973年首次使用<ref name=Ril2011/>。

